Runtime Execution Rules

The Integration Hub processes integrations using this sequence:

1. Authenticate request (JWT)
2. Resolve vendor identity from bcpAuth
3. Check allowlist rules
4. Validate request schema
5. Map request to target vendor format
6. Call downstream vendor API
7. Validate response
8. Map response to caller format
9. Emit audit event
10. Emit usage event

Never bypass validation or allowlist checks.

All runtime executions must emit:
transaction logs
audit events
usage events